                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "Minoxidil is prescribed for a client to treat hair loss. The client asks the nurse if the hair will continue to grow when the medication is stopped. What is the appropriate nursing response?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nHair regrowth with the use of minoxidil is most likely to occur when baldness has developed recently and has been limited to a small area. Benefits of the medication take several months. On discontinuation of the medication, newly gained hair is lost in 3 to 4 months, and the natural progression of hair loss resumes. Options 1 and 3 are incorrect. Option 4 places the client's question on hold and is inappropriate.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nUse therapeutic communication techniques. Option 4 can be eliminated easily because it places the client's question on hold. Knowledge regarding the clinical response and effects of this medication is required to select the correct answer from the remaining options.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Cardiovascular: Vasodilators\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Implementation\nPriority Concepts: Cellular Regulation, Patient Education\nStrategies: Therapeutic Communication Techniques",
                        "id": "a6dfcdbffeca41e9be1a8571632bcd33",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "982c7faeb5264ef1abff6ca90236bc54",
                                "content": "The client will have an increase in urine output."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "3085abda4ae743e0ad40fee41f7980da",
                                "content": "The client will have an absence of dysrhythmias."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "534cb2ea7371445b8bc04d5071d363ce",
                                "content": "The client will have an increase in blood pressure."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "438bf2d0db1c4312bd97065396b0518d",
                                "content": "The client will have an increase in pulmonary capillary wedge pressure."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
